{"title": "Unsanitized user input in HTTP send file request", "summary": " Passing unsanitized user input to the sendFile API is bad practice and can lead to path manipulation, by which attackers can gain access to resources and data outside of the intended scope. ", "description": "\nPassing unsanitized user input to the sendFile API is bad practice and can lead to path manipulation, by which attackers can gain access to resources and data outside of the intended scope.\n", "recommendations": "\n\u2705 Set the root option to be an absolute path to a directory\n\n```javascript\napp.post(\"/upload\", (req, res) => {\n  var options = {\n    root: path.join(__dirname, \"upload\")\n  }\n  res.sendFile(req.params.filename, options)\n}\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-73"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_express_external_file_upload", "http://expressjs.com/en/5x/api.html#res.sendFile"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}